// NOTE: Integrated into the Fusion FSN tree for migration traceability.
// CONTENT:
// Product Guide: Fusion Runtime Core v3.0 (Supernova)Component ID: F-RUNTIME-V3Classification: Kernel Bypass RuntimeAuthor: Systems Lead1. Vision & PurposeSupernova (v3.0) is the pinnacle of the Reactor evolution. It treats the OS as a mere bootloader, bypassing the kernel's network and scheduling stacks to achieve sub-microsecond latency.2. Technical Replacement SpecsReplaces: Linux Kernel Scheduler, epoll, standard TCP stack.Mechanism: Userspace Hardware Polling.3. Technical DetailKernel Bypass: Uses isolcpus and irqbalance to seize control of physical CPU cores.Busy-Polling: Instead of waiting for interrupts, Supernova spins on the NIC's completion queue using io_uring.Zero-Copy: Data moves from the network card directly into Fusion Core Arenas without ever entering kernel memory.4. Why this existsFor High-Frequency Trading (HFT) and ultra-low-latency telecommunications where a 5µs context switch is unacceptable.
